Third Department,

November, 1950.

(November 15, 1950.) In the Matter of Charles H. Van Buren, Jr., et al., Copartners Doing Business under the Name of Van’s Spotless Dairy, Petitioners, against C. Chester Du Mond, as Commissioner of Agriculture and Markets of the State of New York, Respondent.

Motion to dismiss proceeding granted, by default. Present — ■ Foster, P. J., Heffernan, Deyo, Bergan and Coon, JJ.
